<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-056-171 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 466 864</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 23 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New PC: office in briefcase for UK. (Business ComputingConsultants offers integrated notebook computer and computerprinter system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Business Computing Consultants (Products).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyInk-Jet PrintersIntegrated SystemsNotebook computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW PC: Office In Briefcase For UK 09/23/91 LONDON, ENGLAND, 1991 SEP 23 (NB)-- Business Computing Consultants (BCC) has launched &quot;the office in abriefcase,&quot; a portable PC plus bubble jet printer combination that thecompany claims is everything a mobile executive requires to becomeself-sufficient in and out of the office or home.andM;&quot;There's no more struggling with several items, going back to the office toprint out documents or worrying about finding a recharger,&quot; said Mark Jones,BCC's managing director.andM;The idea behind the office in a briefcase came to Jones when he found himselfin just this situation in consultancy work.andP;  &quot;It was clear that recenttechnological innovations provided all the necessary power for the office ina briefcase.andP;  Other attempts, however, ignored the importance of aesthetics,&quot;he said.andM;&quot;Until now, the innovations were all too commonly perceived as gadgets -often difficult to carry or use - in search of a real marketing solution.andO;The result was wasted power, money and time,&quot; he added.andM;The &quot;office in a briefcase&quot; consists of a 40MB hard disk-equipped PC with gasplasma screen plus a Canon Bubblejet BJ10e printer.andP;  UKP 2,895 gets thesystem with 2MB of RAM - UKP 100 extra for the 4MB RAM option.andM;(Steve Gold/19910920/Press andamp; Public Contact: Business Computing Consultants -Tel: 0962-732070)</TEXT></DOC>